com.usc.bill.dto

Class Course

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.usc.bill.dto.Course

  • public class Course
extends java.lang.Object
    A course is an academic class associated with a Student, the number of courses and attributes such as the number of credit hours will be used to calculate the student’s bill.

    • Field Detail

      • id

        private java.lang.String id
        The id of a course is the unique identifier of the course, e.g. "CSCE 740".

      • name

        private java.lang.String name
        The name is the short string description of a course, e.g. "Sofware Processes".

      • numCredits

        private int numCredits
        The numCredits is the number of credit hours of the course, e.g. 3. A student's bill is calculated in part by the number of credit hours enrolled by the student.

      • online

        private boolean online
        online is a Boolean flag used to indicate if the course is taken physically on campus, or remotely via the web. Additional charges are typically incurred for online courses.
